<subSubSection lastPageId="51" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="50.[189,1399,1465,1984]" lastBlockId="51.[242,1399,267,323]" lastPageId="51" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Kukuev E. I. &amp; Parin N. V. &amp; Trunov I. A." box="[393,624,1864,1888]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="185 - 199" refId="ref40826" refString="Kukuev E. I., Parin N. V. &amp; Trunov I. A. 2012. Materials for the revision of the Family Caristiidae (Perciformes). 2. Manefishes from the East Atlantic (Redescription of Platyberyx opalescens Zugmayer and description of two new species Platyberyx mauli sp. n. and Caristius andriashevi sp. n.). Journal of Ichthyology 52 (3): 185 - 199. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1134 / S 0032945212010080" type="journal article" year="2012">
Kukuev 
<emphasis box="[486,541,1864,1888]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
, reliable catches of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zugmayer" authorityYear="1911" box="[843,988,1864,1888]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Caristiidae" genus="Platyberyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="opalescens">
<emphasis box="[843,988,1864,1888]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">P. opalescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1180,1270,1864,1888]" name="Portugal" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Portugal</collectingCountry>
to northern 
<collectingCountry box="[242,359,1896,1920]" name="Mauritania" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Mauritania</collectingCountry>
and suggest that the range of the species includes the near-bottom waters of the continental slope (bathial-pelagic ichthyocene) of the East Atlantic. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Santos R. S. &amp; Porteiro F. M. &amp; Barreiros J. P." box="[948,1169,1928,1952]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="1 - 244" refId="ref43831" refString="Santos R. S., Porteiro F. M. &amp; Barreiros J. P. 1997. Marine fishes of the Azores: annotated checklist and bibliography. Arquipelago - Life and Marine Sciences. Suppl. 1: 1 - 244." type="journal article" year="1997">
Santos 
<emphasis box="[1029,1086,1928,1952]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">et al.</emphasis>
(1997)
</bibRefCitation>
, the presence of this species off the Azores is based on the identification of a 
<quantity box="[829,903,1960,1984]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.3" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" unit="mm" value="63.0">63 mm</quantity>
specimen caught by the R/V “Michael Sars” at 
<geoCoordinate box="[242,368,267,291]" degrees="29.7833" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" precision="5" value="-29.7833">29.7833º W</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[377,496,267,291]" degrees="36.8833" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" precision="5" value="36.8833">36.8833º N</geoCoordinate>
(St. 56). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Eschmeyer W. N." box="[737,932,267,291]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refId="ref39931" refString="Eschmeyer W. N. (ed.) 2013. The Catalog of Fishes. California Academy of Sciences, San Francisco, California, U. S. A. Available from: http: // researcharchive. calacademy. org / research / ichthyology / catalog / fishcatmain. asp and http: // collections. calacademy. org / ich /" type="url" year="2013">Eschmeyer (2013)</bibRefCitation>
the range of the species is wider (
<collectingCountry box="[1286,1399,267,291]" name="Greenland" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Greenland</collectingCountry>
and eastern Atlantic).
</paragraph>
